A cave entrance is used to enter the Underground Pass from Tirannwn. It can be found at the eastern edge of Tirannwn, just north of Lletya and south of Arandar. Inside is a small cave containing an altar and the Well of Voyage, which transports players to Iban's Temple in the Underground Pass. Players enter the Tirannwn forests for the first time through this entrance during Regicide. During Song of the Elves, Lady Trahaearn can be found hidden in a crevice within the cave.

Presumably this was the same entrance used by the elves to access the Underground Pass in the past.

A '''cave entrance''' is used to enter the [[Underground Pass]] from [[Tirannwn]]. It can be found at the eastern edge of Tirannwn, just north of [[Lletya]] and south of [[Arandar]]. Inside is a small cave containing an altar and the [[Well of Voyage]], which transports players to [[Iban's Temple]] in the Underground Pass. Players enter the Tirannwn forests for the first time through this entrance during [[Regicide]]. During [[Song of the Elves]], [[Lady Trahaearn]] can be found hidden in a crevice within the cave.

Presumably this was the same entrance used by the elves to access the Underground Pass in the past.
